data.title: A book that made you say appreciate the author’s cleverness?? For me, the one that comes to mind right away is Fifteen Dogs by Andre...
data.meta_description:
13 likes, 2 comments - booksandreadit on June 14, 2024: "A book that made you say appreciate the author’s cleverness?? For me, the one that comes to mind right away is Fifteen Dogs by Andre Alexis. It’s such a fun but thoughtful book written from the perspective of the dogs. I really enjoyed it.

Here is Reddit’s pick:
- Flatland: A Romance of Many Dimensions by Edwin Abbott Abbott
- Sirens of Titan by Kurt Vonnegut
- Remarkably Bright Creatures by Shelby Van Pelt
- The Murder of Roger Ackroyd by Agatha Christie
- Life after Life by Kate Aitkinson
- The Seven Deaths of Evelyn Hardcastle

Have you read any of these? If yes, which one and what are your thoughts? Is there a book you’d want to suggest?!
